Diet

Diet is just as important for animals as humans for their overall health! I feed as natural and healthy as possible, nothing but premium food such as Open farm and fresh foods that I cook and bake for them. Before and during pregnancies I feed an organic blend of prenatal vitamins to help ensure the best possible chance of a healthy pregnancy and delivery for my dams and their puppies.
Open Farm provides human-grade quality food, employs small farms, and produces a very healthy dog food! I feed open farm food to all my adult dogs and puppies. One of the best parts of open farm is there ingredients list is all able to be traced back to its source through their website. With Open Farm you know exactly what's in our furry friend's food and exactly where it came from.

What Not To Feed

My general rule of thumb for dog treats or any dog foods is if Walmart sells it i don't feed it. Not because of Walmart but because of the food & treat quality. The only food I would ever come close to recommending from Walmart is a fresh pet select, you should be safe with pretty much any of the fresh pet select food options. Most Human food is bad to feed your furry family member and one of the biggest reasons is sodium. Most human foods contain a signifact amount of soduium and this can lead to heart failure and other seroius health issues and signifactly shorten a dogs life span. Every puppy comes with a informational guide on what human foods are good to feed your new family member and what foods are not!

Other Foods

The only other food type item I recommend is called no hide from Earth Animals. No hide is a rawhide alternative that won't wreak havoc on your furry friend's digestive track as rawhides will. No hide is a great healthy Chewying treat that I make sure I always have around, It is one of the only things I can buy that they can't chew up in 20 mins and its made with healthy ingredients!

); } export default AboutDiet;
